edu.clarke.team2988.commands

Class CommandBase

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command.Command
      • edu.clarke.team2988.commands.CommandBase
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NamedSendable, Sendable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AutoDriveCommand, AxisShootCommand, CameraCommand, CompressorCommand, DriveCommand, ExampleCommand, FireCommand, HeightCommand, LifterCommand, ResetHeightCommand, ShootCommand, ShootStopCommand

    public abstract class CommandBase
extends Command
    The base for all commands. All atomic commands should subclass CommandBase. CommandBase stores creates and stores each control system. To access a subsystem elsewhere in your code in your code use the getters provided in this class. The getters are implemented as "public static" methods so an instance of this class is not required to access them.

    Example: CommandBase.getShooterSubsystem();

    For questions, see one of the authors

    Author:
    Micheal Dowling, Emily Snyder, Dennis Heflin
    See Also:
    {@link edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command.Subsystem Subsystem}, {@link OI OI}
